list_definition_mean.definitions_word_en: the side or part of an object that presents itself to view or that is normally seen or used first; the most forward part of something.
list_definition_mean.definitions_ex_en: a page at the front of the book had been torn out
list_definition_mean.definitions_ex_vn: một trang ở phía trước của cuốn sách đã bị xé ra

list_definition_mean.definitions_word_en: the foremost line or part of an armed force; the furthest position that an army has reached and where the enemy is or may be engaged.
list_definition_mean.definitions_ex_en: his regiment was immediately sent to the front
list_definition_mean.definitions_ex_vn: Trung đoàn của anh ta ngay lập tức được gửi đến phía trước

list_definition_mean.definitions_word_en: an appearance or form of behavior assumed by a person to conceal their genuine feelings.
list_definition_mean.definitions_ex_en: she put on a brave front
list_definition_mean.definitions_ex_vn: Cô ấy đặt trên một mặt trước dũng cảm

list_definition_mean.definitions_ex_en: he's got a bit of talent and a lot of front
list_definition_mean.definitions_ex_vn: Anh ấy có một chút tài năng và rất nhiều phía trước

list_definition_mean.definitions_ex_en: the front cover of the magazine

list_definition_mean.definitions_word_en: (of a vowel sound) formed by raising the tongue, excluding the blade and tip, toward the hard palate.
(of a building or piece of land) have the front facing or directed toward.
list_definition_mean.definitions_ex_en: the houses that front Beacon Street
list_definition_mean.definitions_ex_vn: những ngôi nhà mà đường Beacon phía trước

list_definition_mean.definitions_word_en: provide (something) with a front or facing of a particular type or material.
list_definition_mean.definitions_ex_en: a metal box fronted by an alloy panel
list_definition_mean.definitions_ex_vn: một hộp kim loại phía trước bởi một bảng hợp kim

list_definition_mean.definitions_word_en: lead or be the most prominent member in (an organization, activity, or group of musicians).
list_definition_mean.definitions_ex_en: the group is fronted by two girl singers
list_definition_mean.definitions_ex_vn: Nhóm được hai ca sĩ cô gái phía trước

list_definition_mean.definitions_word_en: act as a front or cover for someone or something acting illegally or wishing to conceal something.
list_definition_mean.definitions_ex_en: he fronted for them in illegal property deals
list_definition_mean.definitions_ex_vn: Ông đứng trước cho họ trong các giao dịch bất động sản bất hợp pháp

list_definition_mean.definitions_word_en: articulate (a vowel sound) with the tongue further forward.
list_definition_mean.definitions_ex_en: all speakers use raised and fronted variants more in spontaneous speech
list_definition_mean.definitions_ex_vn: Tất cả các loa sử dụng các biến thể được nâng lên và phía trước nhiều hơn trong bài phát biểu tự phát

list_definition_mean.definitions_word_en: place (a sentence element) at the beginning of a sentence instead of in its usual position, typically for emphasis or as a feature of some dialects, as in horrible it was.
used to summon someone to the front or to command them to assume a forward-facing position, as in calling a bellhop to the front desk or giving orders to troops on parade.
list_definition_mean.definitions_ex_vn: Hướng đạo sinh, phía trước và trung tâm!
